<item>
            <title>[LU-13023] PCC: The size of the PCC copy is not truncated to 0 when attach</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13023</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the Linux kernel, it seems that dentry_open() with O_TRUNC flag (i.e. Ext4) does not&#160;take effect to truncate the size of the PCC copy to zero. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This may result in incorrect size for PCC copy in the following test cases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Attach a file with size of s1 (s2 &amp;gt; 0) into PCC;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;detach this file with --keep option, and the data will retain on PCC;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;truncate this file locally or on an remote client to the size s2 (s2 &amp;lt; s1);&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;re-attach the file again.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This problem is solved by reset the file size of the PCC copy to 0 after open the PCC copy during attach.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
